summary.name: S&P 500 Historical Data
summary.dataset_description: This dataset contains historical data of the S&P 500 index from 2000 to 2020, including date, open, high, low, close, adjusted close, and volume.

properties.description: The date of the trading day.
The opening price of the S&P 500 index on the trading day.
The highest price of the S&P 500 index during the trading day.
The lowest price of the S&P 500 index during the trading day.
The closing price of the S&P 500 index on the trading day.
The adjusted closing price of the S&P 500 index on the trading day, accounting for dividends and stock splits.
The total trading volume of the S&P 500 index on the trading day.

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='volume', bins=50, color='blue', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['volume'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['volume'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Trading Volume')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of daily trading volume?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(x='open', y='close', data=data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['daily_change'] = data['adjclose'].diff()
    data['avg_daily_change'] = data['daily_change'].mean()

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='daily_change', data=data, label='Daily Change')
    plt.axhline(data['avg_daily_change'], color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Average Daily Change: {data['avg_daily_change'].round(2)}")
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Adjusted Closing Price Change')
    plt.title('What is the average daily change in the adjusted closing price?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.boxplot(data=data[['high', 'low']])
    plt.title("What is the distribution of daily high and low prices?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend(['High', 'Low'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='volume', y='adjclose', hue='date', palette='viridis', legend='full')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between trading volume and price?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Trading Volume')
    plt.ylabel('Adjusted Close Price')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Date', loc='upper right', bbox_to_anchor=(1.2, 1))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
